                        </tr>
                    </table>
                </div>
                <p>Dial <strong>*400#</strong> to get any package information and check internet balance</p>
                <h2>To Add a number to your Shared Internet Plan:</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>For  Postpaid:</strong>To add a  postpaid number to your Shared Internet Plan, SMS <strong>Add &lt;space&gt; number</strong>to <strong>4000</strong>.</li>
                    <li>Only two numbers can  be added to the Shared Internet Plans in a single day.</li>
                </ul>
                <h2>To Delete a number from your Shared Internet  Plan:</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>For  Postpaid:</strong>To delete a  postpaid number from your Shared Internet Plan, SMS <strong>Del &lt;space&gt; number </strong>to <strong>4000</strong>.</li>
                    <li>If a postpaid customer  is not willing to accept the Shared Internet Plan offer, SMS <strong>Noshare to  4000</strong>.</li>
                    <li>SMS charges shall be  applicable.</li>
                </ul>
                <h2>Terms and Conditions:</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Shared Internet Plans  can be availed by both Warid 2G and LTE customers.</li>
                    <li>No charges will be  deducted for adding numbers to your shared internet plans. This is a limited time offer  only.</li>
                    <!--<li>You can also manage  your Shared Internet Plan from our latest MyWarid App. Activate your plan, add  or delete numbers by downloading the app now.<br>
                          Click here: <a href="http://www.waridtel.com/lte/vas/mywarid">http://www.waridtel.com/lte/vas/mywarid</a> </li>-->
                    <li>You can also activate your plan add or delete number by downloading our latest <a href="../../lte/vas/mywarid.html">My Warid App</a> or Visit our self-service web portal. <a href="http://internet.waridtel.com/" target="_blank">http://internet.waridtel.com/</a></li>
                    <li>Secondary numbers will  be charged as per their individual package or default rate in case Shared  Internet Plan subscriber’s internet bundle is consumed.</li>
                    <li>Shared Internet Plans  can be consumed amongst three devices only. One primary user/subscriber can  have up to&nbsp;2 secondary shared numbers only.</li>
                    <li>Sharing can be defined  only among postpaid numbers if the primary subscriber is postpaid.</li>
                    <li>For more details, call  321 or visit your nearest Warid Business Center or Franchise.</li>
                </ul>
